{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782365617077,"sessionID":"ses_102be2c3dffeRyA4IsDHFUpioX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_89lLm8dWFEDajjMfUT81dytf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\agent-inputs\\phase02-data-repository-row-patch.json"},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\agent-inputs\\phase02-data-repository-row-patch.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"schemaVersion\": 1,\n3:   \"purpose\": \"Close the phase-02 data/repository observable startup-state row after wiring the real runtime startup path through LoginPreferencesService and StartupStore.\",\n4:   \"updates\": [\n5:     {\n6:       \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-data-repository-lo-7dc1a245fb-003-observable-state-viewmodel-flow-livedata\",\n7:       \"set\": {\n8:         \"status\": \"implemented\",\n9:         \"parityLevel\": \"equivalent\",\n10:         \"targetBehavior\": \"LoginPreferencesService.readLoginState now feeds StartupStore.resolveStartRoute during EntryAbility.onCreate, and the resolved route seeds bootstrapStartRoute before FoodikeBootstrap loads. This preserves the source one-shot observable startup contract: the persisted login flag is read before loading clears and before the shell becomes interactive.\",\n11:         \"verificationEvidence\": [\n12:           \"Manual code review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/login_preferences_service.cj::LoginPreferencesService.readLoginState, entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/startup/startup_store.cj::StartupStore.resolveStartRoute, and entry/src/main/cangjie/app_ability.cj::EntryAbility.onCreate now form the runtime startup chain that reads the persisted login flag and resolves the first route before bootstrap content loads.\",\n13:           \"Manual code review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.currentRoute initializes from bootstrapStartRoute, so the first rendered shell route matches the resolved startup state.\",\n14:           \"Test verification: `cjpm.exe test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` passed in `D:\\\\workspace\\\\Foodike\\\\Foodike-Harmony\\\\entry` with the phase test env overlay, covering entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj including `resolvesLoggedOutUsersToOnboarding`, `resolvesLoggedInUsersToHome`, and `startupStorePublishesResolvedRouteAndClearsLoading`.\"\n15:         ],\n16:         \"targetEndpoints\": [\n17:           \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/login_preferences_service.cj::LoginPreferencesService.readLoginState\",\n18:           \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/startup/startup_store.cj::StartupStore.resolveStartRoute\",\n19:           \"entry/src/main/cangjie/app_ability.cj::EntryAbility.onCreate\",\n20:           \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.currentRoute\",\n21:           \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj::resolveStartRoute\"\n22:         ],\n23:         \"tests\": [\n24:           \"entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj::Phase02StartupNavigationTest.resolvesLoggedOutUsersToOnboarding\",\n25:           \"entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj::Phase02StartupNavigationTest.resolvesLoggedInUsersToHome\",\n26:           \"entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj::Phase02StartupNavigationTest.startupStorePublishesResolvedRouteAndClearsLoading\"\n27:         ],\n28:         \"notes\": \"Closed as equivalent for phase 02 because the source `Flow<Boolean>` is only consumed once via `first()` during splash initialization, and the target now performs the same one-shot persisted-state-to-route handoff through the repository/store surfaces used at runtime.\"\n29:       }\n30:     }\n31:   ]\n32: }\n\n(End of file - total 32 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"schemaVersion\": 1,\n  \"purpose\": \"Close the phase-02 data/repository observable startup-state row after wiring the real runtime startup path through LoginPreferencesService and StartupStore.\",\n  \"updates\": [\n    {\n      \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-data-repository-lo-7dc1a245fb-003-observable-state-viewmodel-flow-livedata\",\n      \"set\": {\n        \"status\": \"implemented\",\n        \"parityLevel\": \"equivalent\",\n        \"targetBehavior\": \"LoginPreferencesService.readLoginState now feeds StartupStore.resolveStartRoute during EntryAbility.onCreate, and the resolved route seeds bootstrapStartRoute before FoodikeBootstrap loads. This preserves the source one-shot observable startup contract: the persisted login flag is read before loading clears and before the shell becomes interactive.\",\n        \"verificationEvidence\": [\n          \"Manual code review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/login_preferences_service.cj::LoginPreferencesService.readLoginState, entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/startup/startup_store.cj::StartupStore.resolveStartRoute, and entry/src/main/cangjie/app_ability.cj::EntryAbility.onCreate now form the runtime startup chain that reads the persisted login flag and resolves the first route before bootstrap content loads.\",\n          \"Manual code review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.currentRoute initializes from bootstrapStartRoute, so the first rendered shell route matches the resolved startup state.\",\n          \"Test verification: `cjpm.exe test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` passed in `D:\\\\workspace\\\\Foodike\\\\Foodike-Harmony\\\\entry` with the phase test env overlay, covering entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj including `resolvesLoggedOutUsersToOnboarding`, `resolvesLoggedInUsersToHome`, and `startupStorePublishesResolvedRouteAndClearsLoading`.\"\n        ],\n        \"targetEndpoints\": [\n          \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/login_preferences_service.cj::LoginPreferencesService.readLoginState\",\n          \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/startup/startup_store.cj::StartupStore.resolveStartRoute\",\n          \"entry/src/main/cangjie/app_ability.cj::EntryAbility.onCreate\",\n          \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.currentRoute\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\agent-inputs\\phase02-data-repository-row-patch.json","time":{"start":1782365617068,"end":1782365617076}},"id":"prt_efd44fb78001pxY887uEvMzi3s","sessionID":"ses_102be2c3dffeRyA4IsDHFUpioX","messageID":"msg_efd44e87c0015EoHfwxRc80R3B"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782365617118,"sessionID":"ses_102be2c3dffeRyA4IsDHFUpioX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_u3Oe4LIxfstd85khGIjMp22j","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\matrix-batch1-patch.json","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\matrix-batch1-patch.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"updates\": [\n3:     {\n4:       \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-e5fadea668-001-android-resource-configuration-must-be-m\",\n5:       \"set\": {\n6:         \"status\": \"implemented\",\n7:         \"parityLevel\": \"equivalent\",\n8:         \"sourceBehavior\": \"The manifest binds the Foodike application label, launcher icon, splash theme, backup/xml resource references, and launcher activity metadata to Android startup resources.\",\n9:         \"targetBehavior\": \"`AppScope/app.json5`, `entry/src/main/module.json5`, and the target color/media/string resources preserve the app identity, launcher metadata, start-window background/icon, and page profile wiring for the HarmonyOS entry module.\",\n10:         \"notes\": \"Mapped manifest resource/configuration wiring into HarmonyOS app and module metadata instead of Android manifest attributes.\"\n11:       },\n12:       \"append\": {\n13:         \"targetEndpoints\": [\n14:           \"AppScope/app.json5\",\n15:           \"entry/src/main/module.json5\",\n16:           \"entry/src/main/resources/base/element/color.json\",\n17:           \"entry/src/main/resources/base/profile/main_pages.json\"\n18:         ],\n19:         \"verificationEvidence\": [\n20:           \"Source inspection: app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml uses @string/app_name, @mipmap/ic_launcher, and @style/Theme.SplashScreenTheme on the application and launcher activity.\",\n21:           \"Build gate PASS: translation-inputs/build-reports/phase-01-project-skeleton-resources/build-report.md (Generated 2026-06-25T04:33:21+00:00).\"\n22:         ]\n23:       }\n24:     },\n25:     {\n26:       \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-525ca85433-002-intent-uri-bundle-deeplink-or-cross-scre\",\n27:       \"set\": {\n28:         \"status\": \"implemented\",\n29:         \"parityLevel\": \"equivalent\",\n30:         \"sourceBehavior\": \"The manifest defines a single launcher entry point through MAIN/LAUNCHER intent-filter for `MainActivity`; no deeplink, URI pattern, or extra bundle contract is declared here.\",\n31:         \"targetBehavior\": \"`entry/src/main/module.json5` exposes the single HarmonyOS home entry ability with `action.system.home` and `entity.system.home`, preserving the source app's single-launch entry contract without adding deeplink behavior.\",\n32:         \"notes\": \"Closed narrowly to launcher-entry semantics only; source manifest does not declare custom deeplinks.\"\n33:       },\n34:       \"append\": {\n35:         \"targetEndpoints\": [\n36:           \"entry/src/main/module.json5\"\n37:         ],\n38:         \"verificationEvidence\": [\n39:           \"Source inspection: app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml contains only android.intent.action.MAIN and android.intent.category.LAUNCHER for MainActivity.\",\n40:           \"Target inspection: entry/src/main/module.json5 exposes EntryAbility with home skill actions/entities.\"\n41:         ]\n42:       }\n43:     },\n44:     {\n45:       \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-dcc4612e71-003-runtime-permission-request-permission-re\",\n46:       \"set\": {\n47:         \"status\": \"not-applicable\",\n48:         \"parityLevel\": \"not-applicable\",\n49:         \"sourceBehavior\": \"The analyzer flagged runtime permissions from manifest context, but the inspected manifest declares no dangerous permissions and no protected API access contract.\",\n50:         \"targetBehavior\": \"No HarmonyOS permission wiring was added because the source manifest contains no permission declarations or permission result flow to preserve.\",\n51:         \"notes\": \"Closed from direct source inspection as a manifest-level false positive.\"\n52:       },\n53:       \"append\": {\n54:         \"verificationEvidence\": [\n55:           \"Source inspection: app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml contains no <uses-permission> entries and no permission-related activity/provider/service declarations.\"\n56:         ]\n57:       }\n58:     },\n59:     {\n60:       \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-c7c6907eb1-004-android-platform-component-lifecycle-suc\",\n61:       \"set\": {\n62:         \"status\": \"platform-replaced\",\n63:         \"parityLevel\": \"platform-replaced\",\n64:         \"sourceBehavior\": \"The manifest declares an `Application` subclass plus a single launcher `Activity`, establishing the app-level component lifecycle and entry shell for startup.\",\n65:         \"targetBehavior\": \"HarmonyOS replaces the Android application/activity pair with `FoodikeAbilityStage` and `EntryAbility`, keeping a thin lifecycle shell that owns startup logging, preference-backed bootstrap inspection, and window content loading.\",\n66:         \"notes\": \"Platform replacement from Android Application/Activity lifecycle to HarmonyOS AbilityStage/UIAbility lifecycle.\"\n67:       },\n68:       \"append\": {\n69:         \"targetEndpoints\": [\n70:           \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ability_stage.cj::FoodikeAbilityStage.onCreate\",\n71:           \"entry/src/main/cangjie/app_ability.cj::EntryAbility.onCreate\",\n72:           \"entry/src/main/cangjie/app_ability.cj::EntryAbility.onWindowStageCreate\"\n73:         ],\n74:         \"verificationEvidence\": [\n75:           \"Source inspection: app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml declares application .FoodikeApp and launcher activity .presentation.MainActivity.\",\n76:           \"Build gate PASS: translation-inputs/build-reports/phase-01-project-skeleton-resources/build-report.md (CompileCangjie and PackageHap finished).\"\n77:         ]\n78:       }\n79:     },\n80:     {\n81:       \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-422b0d36ae-005-screen-lifecycle-entry-point-initializat\",\n82:       \"set\": {\n83:         \"status\": \"platform-replaced\",\n84:         \"parityLevel\": \"platform-replaced\",\n85:         \"sourceBehavior\": \"The launcher activity starts under `Theme.SplashScreenTheme`, then hands control to the main Compose shell during activity creation.\",\n86:         \"targetBehavior\": \"`EntryAbility.onCreate` and `EntryAbility.onWindowStageCreate` perform the HarmonyOS startup handoff: inspect persisted login preference state during ability creation and load the bootstrap page into the main `WindowStage`.\",\n87:         \"notes\": \"This is startup shell parity only; full routed startup gating remains planned for phase 2.\"\n88:       },\n89:       \"append\": {\n90:         \"targetEndpoints\": [\n91:           \"entry/src/main/cangjie/app_ability.cj::EntryAbility.onCreate\",\n92:           \"entry/src/main/cangjie/app_ability.cj::EntryAbility.onWindowStageCreate\",\n93:           \"entry/src/main/resources/base/profile/main_pages.json\"\n94:         ],\n95:         \"verificationEvidence\": [\n96:           \"Source inspection: MainActivity installs splash screen and sets content in onCreate; manifest/theme wire startup resources.\",\n97:           \"Target inspection: app_ability.cj reads persisted login flag from HarmonyOS Preferences and windowStage.loadContent(\\\"FoodikeBootstrap\\\").\"\n98:         ]\n99:       }\n100:     },\n101:     {\n102:       \"featureId\": \"app-build-gradle-kts-52a26dc1e9-003-android-platform-component-lifecycle-suc\",\n103:       \"set\": {\n104:         \"status\": \"platform-replaced\",\n105:         \"parityLevel\": \"platform-replaced\",\n106:         \"sourceBehavior\": \"`app/build.gradle.kts` configures the Android application module and app-level runtime dependencies that support the launcher activity, Hilt application shell, and splash/navigation entry flow.\",\n107:         \"targetBehavior\": \"`entry/cjpm.toml`, `AppScope/app.json5`, and `entry/src/main/module.json5` replace Android module wiring with a HarmonyOS entry module, ability metadata, and Cangjie package root under `ohos_app_cangjie_entry`.\",\n108:         \"notes\": \"Closed as build/module bootstrap parity rather than Android Gradle syntax parity.\"\n109:       },\n110:       \"append\": {\n111:         \"targetEndpoints\": [\n112:           \"entry/cjpm.toml\",\n113:           \"AppScope/app.json5\",\n114:           \"entry/src/main/module.json5\"\n115:         ],\n116:         \"verificationEvidence\": [\n117:           \"Source inspection: app/build.gradle.kts applies android application, kotlin android, kapt, and hilt plugins for the app module.\",\n118:           \"Build gate PASS: translation-inputs/build-reports/phase-01-project-skeleton-resources/build-report.md.\"\n119:         ]\n120:       }\n\n(Showing lines 1-120 of 349. Use offset=121 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"updates\": [\n    {\n      \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-e5fadea668-001-android-resource-configuration-must-be-m\",\n      \"set\": {\n        \"status\": \"implemented\",\n        \"parityLevel\": \"equivalent\",\n        \"sourceBehavior\": \"The manifest binds the Foodike application label, launcher icon, splash theme, backup/xml resource references, and launcher activity metadata to Android startup resources.\",\n        \"targetBehavior\": \"`AppScope/app.json5`, `entry/src/main/module.json5`, and the target color/media/string resources preserve the app identity, launcher metadata, start-window background/icon, and page profile wiring for the HarmonyOS entry module.\",\n        \"notes\": \"Mapped manifest resource/configuration wiring into HarmonyOS app and module metadata instead of Android manifest attributes.\"\n      },\n      \"append\": {\n        \"targetEndpoints\": [\n          \"AppScope/app.json5\",\n          \"entry/src/main/module.json5\",\n          \"entry/src/main/resources/base/element/color.json\",\n          \"entry/src/main/resources/base/profile/main_pages.json\"\n        ],\n        \"verificationEvidence\": [\n          \"Source inspection: app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml uses @string/app_name, @mipmap/ic_launcher, and @style/Theme.SplashScreenTheme on the application and launcher activity.\",","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\matrix-batch1-patch.json","time":{"start":1782365617113,"end":1782365617117}},"id":"prt_efd44fbad001tziXNwy4zEW2D2","sessionID":"ses_102be2c3dffeRyA4IsDHFUpioX","messageID":"msg_efd44e87c0015EoHfwxRc80R3B"}}
